With increasing the volume ratio of inflow water vapor and UV intensity put, the methanol concentration almost linearly increases, showing that the photocatalytic reduction of carbon dioxide can be conspicuously improved by increasing the
inflow water vapor percentage and light intensity input. As the inflow velocity increases, the methanol overall production rises as well. With the increase of optical fiber deviation, methanol production efficiency will decrease, so it is recommended that the optical fiber is centrally installed in the monolith channel to obtain a high photocatalytic performance.
